Pour about 300ml cold @salted water{300%ml} into a #medium pot{} with a
tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Rice{150%g} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium and cover with the lid.

Cook for ~{10%minutes} then remove from the heat.

Keep covered for ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will
continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @Onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces).

Roughly chop the @Coriander{5%g} (stalks and all).

Cut the @Tomato{1} into 1cm chunks. Zest and quarter the @Lime{1}.

Drain and rinse the @Black Beans{1%pack} and @Sweetcorn{1%pack} (keep separate).

Halve the @Chilli{1} and discard the core and seeds. Finely chop.

Place a pan over medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the sweetcorn, chilli (use less if you don't like spice)
and half the chopped onion.

Fry until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{to taste} and
@pepper{to taste}.

Meanwhile, mash half the beans with a #fork{}.

Once the veg is softened, add the @Chipotle Paste{2%sachet} to the pan
along with the whole and mashed beans.

Add a splash of @water{to taste} and cook for ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

To make your pico de gallo, mix the tomato, coriander and remaining
chopped onion together in a #bowl{}.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and as much
lime juice as you like.

Halve the @Avocado{1} and remove the pit. Cut into chunks (while still
in its skin), then use a #tablespoon{} to scoop out the flesh.

Stir the lime zest into the cooked rice, fluffing it up as you go.
Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Divide your lime rice between bowls.

Top with spoonfuls of the chipotle bean mixture, avocado chunks and pico
de gallo.

Finish with a squeeze of lime juice.

Serve with any remaining lime wedges alongside.

> The burrito is a staple of Tex-Mex cuisine that originates from Ciudad Juárez
> in Mexico. These plant-based burrito bowls are filled with zesty lime rice,
> gorgeous green avocado, chipotle black beans, and another Mexican staple—
> pico de gallo.